cheesecake recette:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DXnxJBCo_Zc&t=635s

recette de base est 20cm
	lets make 15.24 cm
		so half the recipe


Pâte :
- Biscuit Thé : 45 g (73x0.45)
- Spéculoos : 15 g (74x0.25)
- Beurre (fondu) : 30 g
- Cassonade : 6g g
- Zeste 1/4 citron

180C chaleur tournante 13min
	12

added 5g beurre and 10g speculoos

495g cream per

fond beurre dans pyrex
mix biscuits and sugar first, put mixture in pyrex
add in 1/4 lemon zest, butter, mix with fork
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
La crème (tous les ingrédients doivent être à température ambiante) :
- 46g Sucre en poudre 
- 15 Fécule de maïs (Maïzena)
+
- 75g Crème liquide (35% MG) 
- 1 tbsp Extrait de vanille 
let overnight

- Jus 1/4 citron.

- Philadelphia : 200 g
- Crème fraiche épaisse et entière de normandy  (40%) : 100g

- 1 œufs entier

Small bowl : whisk sugar and maizena
Add creme liquide and combine with spatula
Add vanille
add lemon juice
in medium bowl, mix philadelphia and creme fraiche
add in the content of small bowl
whisk 1 egg (in separate bowl) and add it
mix everything


cook at 180c for 17 minutes
	18 this time
cook at 100c for 35 minutes
	50 this time
cook at 30c for 52 minutes
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
Valeur nutritionnelle 
whole cheese cake: 106g glucide
cheese part : 46g sucre + 15g glucide
the biscuit : 45g glucide (no additional speculos and no cassonade)


1/8 part of cheese cake : 13.5g
----
	




----------------------
Coulis :
- Fruits rouges surgelés : 200 g
- Sucre en poudre : 40 g
- Jus d'1/2 citron

------
Tous ingredients temperature ambiante


-----
use measuring scoop thing to flatten the pate

----
dans un bol
add sucre et maizena

25 min 180 statique
	30 minutes next time

30 minutes 180 statique

1h30 110 degrés

1h four éteint


1h30 minutes 100degree
	(The last 30 minutes were at 105 degrees)
	1h30 minutes at 105-110 degrees next time (or more)
	cook more at this step

with the oven stopped 1h30
	added 50 minutes at 50 degrees
